<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Intro</div>

<div class=itemtext>Mega Man 3 is considered by some to be the greatest Mega Man game of all.  It's definitely one if the longest, one of the most uniquely styled, and one of my favorites.  This is actually the game that introduced me to Mega Man.  I happened to go to my brother's friend's house when they were playing it, and I was instantly hooked by the music, the feel of the game, the challenging, themed bosses, and the fact that you were supposed to use a different weapon for each boss.  The cards with Dr. Light's original robt series in the epilogue ade me curious about the series as a whole, and I rented MM4 as soon as it came out so I could play an entire Mega Man game myself.  I became an instant MegaManiac.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Story</div>

<div class=itemtext>Dr. Wily has supposedly defected to Dr. Light's side again, and he is working with ight to build a humongous peace-keeping robot, Gamma.  However, in order to complete construction, they need 8 special metals from mining colonies on various moons of the solar system.  Mining robots on these colonies have suddenly started a rebellion.  Once Mega Man wins, however, instead of going to the Skull Castle, he fights Doc Robot, another weapon-copy specialist who is designed to fill in for other robots during repairs.  He copies the attacks of all 8 robot masters from MM2.  Then, MM confronts Break Man, who appears to be the ringleader.  SPOILER:  However, Break Man retreats, and Dr. Light informs you that Dr. Wily has just stolen Gamma.  Mega Man meets up once again with the Rock Monster and the cloning machine from MM1, and defeats Wily, who is piloting Gamma.  However, this time, the Skull Castle starts to cave in, covering both Mega Man and Wily.  Break Man appears, apparently to help him fight Mega Man, but instead he takes Mega Man back to Dr. Light's lab.  Dr. Light recognizes Blues' whistle, and the player is told that Break Man was actually Proto Man in a mask.  Why he worked with Wily, and then took Mega Man to Dr. Light's lab, is not explained.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Unique Features</div>

<div class=itemtext>Mega Man 3 is the first MM game to have truly SUPERB music.  It's really just as good musically as any other in the series.  The level graphics also seem to have a darker, but very attractive style.  It also has 19 levels, the most of any Mega Man game yet.  It should also be mentioned that the game introduced Rush.  It's also the first of numerous MM games in which Wily is not supposed to be the villain, at least as far as Mega Man knows.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Robots</div>

<div class=itemtext><a href=mm3robots.txt>Official Enemy Names List</a><br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

